data.enText: to make sb feel ashamed or stupid and lose the respect of other people

data.chText: 我不想当着她同事们的面令她难堪。
data.enText: I didn't want to humiliate her in front of her colleagues.

data.chText: 该党在新近的选举中耻辱地失败了。
data.enText: The party was humiliated in the recent elections.

data.chText: 她当众受到指责，丢了面子。
data.enText: She suffered the humiliation of being criticized in public.

simple_means.memory_skill: hum 土，地 + il 向内 + iate 使… → 使人下到地上 → 羞辱

example: He humiliated his colleague by criticising him in front of the boss

value.def: To humiliate someone means to say or do something which makes them feel ashamed or stupid.

example.ex: She had been beaten and humiliated by her husband...
example.tran: 她遭到丈夫的殴打和羞辱。

example.ex: His teacher continually humiliates him in maths lessons.
example.tran: 他的数学老师频频在课上羞辱他。

example.ex: I have never felt so humiliated in my life.
example.tran: 我一生中从未感到如此丢脸。
